How to create a map on Power BI?

Hover with your mouse over to the Map icon under the visualizations tab on the right-hand side and click on it.



The empty Map visualization will appear.  Adjust the size of the map as you see fit.

After Map size has been adjusted, navigate to the Fields icon underneath the Visualizations tab, while making sure the Map visualization has also been selected.

Begin populating your map data by navigating to the Fields tab on the right-hand side. 

 

Select the drop down icon on the “Dim_Property” tab and the column names for that table should appear.

 

First, we need to create a hierarchy.

Begin by right-clicking the PropertyState column and clicking on “New Hierarchy”.

Your result will yield a new Hierarchy column as seen below.


Right click on the PropertyCity  navigate to “Add to Hierarchy” and click on “PropertyState Hierarchy”

 

Your results should yield the image below for the Property State and City hierarchy.



Click on the “PropertyState Heirarchy” Column and a check mark will appear on this column as well it will appear on the Location selection under the Fields icon.

*Note* After selecting the “PropertyState Heirarchy” you may have to adjust the size of the map again as performed prior.

*Note* Make sure the Map on the page is selected to add values in the Field icon.

 

You can also click and drag on a column and move it to the appropriate selection.  Drag the PropertyCity column to the Legend under the fields icon.


Next, click on the “Key Measures” to view the measures created in the same fields tab.






Drag and drop the “%OfRepeatGuests” measure to the Size and the “% Profit Margin” to the Tooltip under the Field icon.




You will have a final Map result as seen below.



https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/power-bi/guided-learning/visualizations?tutorial-step=5 How to create a map on Power BI?
